<TEXT>
when michelle and rodney lawrence 
got married they really didnt anticipate spending their first 
anniversary on thanksgiving day driving trucks in different parts 
of saudi arabia thousands of miles from their 3monthold son 
for pvt 1 michelle lawrence the best thanksgiving present 
would be to see her 25yearold husband a 3hour drive away in 
the northern desert and to get home as quickly as possible to her 
infant son and two older children 
though some military couples have thrived here others like the 
lawrences have been torn between military duty and family 
commitments back home 
the huge us deployment in the persian gulf shattered mrs 
lawrences family heightened her anxiety and turned her against 
the army which ordered her to leave rodney jr when he was only 
five weeks old 
they said you signed a contract you have to go she said 
i dont think its fair that they split families up like this 
because not everybody needs to be here its extremely 
heartless 
if she had the opportunity the 21yearold from battle creek 
mich said she would choose a peaceful stateside job and quit the 
army 
when i joined the army i never believed id be in a place 
like this back home is such a beautiful place when things come up 
like this it brings reality to the job that youre actually 
doing she said 
mrs lawrence candidly admits she joined the army so she could 
go to college become a lawyer and get comprehensive health 
coverage for her children 
she signed up for 6 years and has been in for 2 years driving 
trucks 
on nov 22 1989 she married fellow truck driver spec rodney 
lawrence and started a new life excited at the prospect of 
completing more prelaw courses 
we used to be in the same unit she said when we got 
married according to military laws they split us up 
their first child was born just after iraq invaded kuwait on 
aug 2 
shortly afterward lawrences 96th transportation company was 
ordered to saudi arabia then 2 weeks later her 180th 
transportation battalion from ft hood tex was deployed here 
i knew i had to go so i volunteered to come with our advance 
party so i could hurry up get over here get it over with and get 
back home she said 
but with no rotations because of the additional us troops 
being deployed here she said those who arrived first will end up 
staying longer 
before lawrence left he adopted her two oldest children tony 
3 and brandon 2 his mother is now looking after them and the 
baby rodney jr 
ive talked to them one time on the phone since ive been 
here the oldest one isnt doing too bad the middle one is really 
taking it hard hes always talking about momma i want you to 
come home momma i miss you momma come get me 
its hard to talk to him i try and talk to tony as long as i 
can to make up for the tears that i shed with brandon 
since her arrival about seven weeks ago mrs lawrence has been 
driving fiveton trucks some of her female colleagues have been 
run off the road or stoned by saudi men unaccustomed to seeing 
women drivers but she said so far shes been lucky 
her husband has been driving tank carriers 
ive seen him three or four times and i get a letter about 
every two or three days she said weve tried to spend as much 
time alone as we possibly could just talking and crying and 
talking about our three children we have back home 
</TEXT>
