president but if we are to make progress there must be an 
immediate recognition by the management at each individual plant of 
the full extent of the problem 
a spokeswoman said gm would have no immediate comment 
repetitive motion traumas also referred to as cumulative trauma 
disorders are disorders of the musculoskeletal and nervous systems 
caused by repetitive motions or exertion over extended periods 
painful and sometimes crippling they range from back injuries 
to a nerve disorder of the hand and wrist to various tendon 
ailments they comprise about 48 percent of the workplace injuries 
for which the departments occupational safety and health 
administration keeps records 
preventive measures include redesigning work stations t better 
accommodate the body by for example adjusting workbench heights 
also devices can be used to prevent excessive lifting or similar 
exertions tools and training can be redesigned 
 
 
