<TEXT>
hindus mourning victims of a massacre by 
sikh separatists attacked a bus station today and assaulted sikhs 
witnesses and police said 
a fourhour curfew was imposed in some sections of amritsar 
following the violence which injured at least two sikhs some of 
the hindus were armed with swords and sticks united news of india 
reported 
at least 11 hindus and two sikhs were killed in a crowded market 
on tuesday evening when masked sikh gunmen opened fire four 
militants suspected to be among the assailants were killed by 
police a few hours later 
amritsar police chief sanjeev gupta said the mourners burned two 
government buses when the funeral procession passed a bus station 
on the way to a cremation ground sikh employees at the bus station 
retaliated by throwing stones said gupta 
the curfew was lifted after the victims of the attack were 
cremated under police guard 
tuesdays attack in amritsar 250 miles northwest of new delhi 
was the latest in a series of killings by separatists in 
strifetorn punjab state 
gupta was quoted by the news agency as saying the weapons 
recovered from the slain radicals tuesday matched spent bullets 
found at the scene of the market shooting 
witnesses had said they saw at least five masked gunmen during 
the attack it was not immediately clear if only four were involved 
or if one had escaped 
at least 120 people have died since nov 13 victims have 
included passengers pulled out of a bus and shot people on morning 
walks and members of security forces 
sikhs comprise just 2 percent of indias 880 million people but 
are in a majority in punjab a rich farming state which borders 
pakistan 
sikh militants have been campaigning for independence since 
1982 claiming their community is discriminated against by the 
hindus who make up 82 percent of the countrys population 
at least 2860 people have been killed in punjab this year in 
violence blamed on the militants 
</TEXT>
