border guards today killed 12 moslem 
militants after the separatists sneaked into india from pakistan 
carrying arms and ammunition officials said 
five militants were captured after the encounter the officials 
said they said 11 sovietdesigned ak47 assault rifles 3200 
bullets 29 grenades and three rocket launchers were seized 
the officials who cannot be identified under briefing rules 
said the group of 17 kashmiri militants was intercepted by troops 
of the paramilitary border security force in kupwara 45 miles west 
of srinagar 
when asked to stop the militants fired forcing the troops to 
return fire the officials said 
officials regularly report similar encounters between border 
guards and moslem militants who the government says receive arms 
and military training in pakistan to carry on their campaign for 
the secession of jammukashmir state from india 
pakistan denies it is training kashmiri militants but says it 
morally supports the insurgency calling it a movement for 
selfdetermination 
the extremists who earlier wanted jammukashmir to unite with 
pakistan now demand indepdence for the moslemmajority state 
sixtyfour percent of the states 6 million people are moslem 
nationwide moslems comprise 12 percent of indias 880 million 
people hindus comprise 82 percent 
at least 1573 people have been killed in kashmir since january 
most of the victims have been militants who fell to security 
forces 
the separatist movement had been simmering since 1947 when 
britishruled india won independence and was partitioned into 
pakistan and india 
jammukashmir then an independent state ruled by a hindu king 
had the option of merging with either pakistan or india the ruler 
chose india pakistan an islamic country says it should have got 
kashmir because of its predominantly moslem population 
