soviet founder vladimir lenin approved the 
executions of czar nicholas ii and his family in 1918 according to 
new evidence published in the most widely read soviet publication 
the latest edition of the weekly arguments and facts quotes 
scholar eduard radzinsky as saying the signatures of lenin and 
fellow leader yakov sverdlov were on a telegram about the execution 
of the czars family sent to local authorities in ekaterinburg 
the newspaper which has a circulation of 327 million quotes 
former bolshevik leader leon trotsky as writing in his diary that 
the decision was taken in moscow and with the direct 
participation of lenin 
the disclosure of lenins involvement suspected by western 
historians and reported earlier this year in the weekly soviet 
magazine ogonyok is sure to further tarnish the nearholy image 
of the founder of the soviet state 
under the sardonic headline toward a bloody battle lyrics 
from a famous soviet revolutionary song arguments and facts said 
soviet citizens had been misled about who was behind the murders 
it illustrated the article with an iconlike representation of 
nicholas ii 
in july 1918 soldiers acting on bolshevik orders shot nicholas 
and his family in a basement in the ural mountains city of 
sverdlovsk then called ekaterinburg nicholas born in 1868 was 
forced to abdicate in march 1917 as revolutionary discontent swept 
russia 
the communists seized power in november 1917 
for 72 years there was a myth that the decision to shoot the 
czar and his family was taken in ekaterinburg by local authorities 
lenin and the government in moscow found out about it only after it 
happened arguments and facts quoted radzinsky as saying 
lenin has been increasingly criticized in some publications and 
demonstrations in the soviet union 
in what is called red terror lenin is accused of creating 
the soviet secret police and the network of labor camps that came 
to be known later as the gulag 
