europes leaders wednesday pledged to replace the 
cold war with an era of peace and unity but left unresolved 
several bitter disputes 
the final document of the 34nation summit made no mention for 
example of the three baltic republics which were excluded from 
the threeday conference despite strenuous lobbying efforts 
it skirted the issue of cyprus which remains divided unlike 
eastern europe the foreign army occupying part of cyprus 
turkeys is not in the process of withdrawing 
yugoslav president borisav jovic in his address to the summit 
spoke of the need to improve the status of national minorities but 
