the general accounting office an investigating arm of congress 
said some shortcomings uncovered in 1985 inspections at the 
departments los alamos argonne sandia and savannah river sites 
went uncorrected for five years 
it said the department gave the argonne facility an 
unsatisfactory rating over the fiveyear period but continued to 
rate security at the others as satisfactory 
the gao report was requested by the house energy subcommittee on 
oversight and investigation and by sens pete domenici rnm and 
jeff bingaman dnm after a 10week strike by the contract 
security force at the los alamos national laboratory last year 
the congressional investigators said many guards hired as 
replacements during the strike did not have the required skills 
they also said an unannounced exercise conducted in april showed 
that 75 per cent of the regular security force failed at one or 
more of the skills required 
for example when the participants encountered an adversarial 
situation many failed to stay behind cover and assess the 
situation the report said instead they left their cover and 
walked up to the potential adversaries to ask what they were 
doing 
