<TEXT>
here are details of the six counts to which 
former drexel burnham lambert inc junk bond executive michael 
milken pleaded guilty 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
milken conspired with former speculator ivan boesky and fund 
manager david solomon from 1984 to late 1986 to manipulate 
securities prices rig transactions evade taxes and regulatory 
requirements and enrich drexel 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
milken in 1984 and 1985 encouraged boesky to buy more than 10 
percent of fishbach corp which was the target of a takeover 
attempt by drexel client victor posner milken agreed to make up 
any losses to boesky drexels interest in boeskys holdings in 
fishbach was not disclosed to the sec 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
milken enlisted the boesky organization to artificially support 
the price of mca inc common stock in late 1984 while drexel client 
golden ngget inc sold its mca holdings milken assured boesky 
that drexel would make up any losses 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
drexel through milken agreed to buy more than 1 million shares 
of helmerich amp payne corp common stock in 1985 from the boesky 
organization but boesky remained responsible for any losses the 
arrangement allowed boesky to claim falsely that his organization 
complied with sec net capital requirements 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
milken agreed with solomon manager of the finsbury fund an 
investment fund for foreigners to overcharge clients in 1985 and 
1986 to recoup fees paid to drexel brokers who sold shares in the 
fund 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
milken engaged in a series of prearranged securities trades to 
help solomon claim false trading losses and reduce his 1985 income 
taxes 
</TEXT>
