agreed to hold a hearing that could have led to a trial and 
conviction 
price who at one time issued a call to arms over the choice 
of a police chief and police officer robert bernal reached a truce 
during 12 hours of talks late tuesday and early wednesday 
bernal emerged from the talks saying he wanted the district 
attorney to drop the case and a grand jury later agreed 
both commissioner price and officer bernal wish the incident 
had never occurred and apologize to the citizens of dallas that 
their actions contributed to discord at a time when the city needed 
harmony price and bernal said in a joint statement wednesday 
bernal had told his superiors that price pointed an uzi gun at 
his head in retaliation for an insult the officer yelled at price 
as he jogged past the commissioners home price contended he was 
holding a pellet gun which he denies pointing at bernal 
for his part price said officer bernal is probably one of 
many police officers who have been thrust into communities that 
they probably know nothing about and have frustrations that are 
mounting 
acting police chief sam gonzales said an internal affairs 
investigation into bernals conduct was continuing but he 
indicated discipline for bernal could be tempered by his efforts to 
resolve his dispute with price 
we would be remiss if we didnt look at what he may have done 
to ease the tensions in this city gonzales said 
bernals lawyer bob baskett said wednesday he was not 
surprised that police would continue their internal investigation 
it causes me no concern because we are confident that such 
an investigation will not result in any disciplinary action against 
bernal he said 
some civic leaders have said the recent discord surrounding the 
incident could threaten a dec 8 vote on a proposed 
singlememberdistrict city council system that proponents say 
would allow minorities more voice in the citys government 
