<TEXT>
drummer buddy rich made his show business debut 
at 18 months singer mel torme who has just finished writing 
richs biography waited until he was 4 before becoming a 
professional entertainer 
torme talked to a lot of people for traps the drum wonder 
including rich artie shaw johnny carson tenor saxophonist 
georgie auld and singer jo stafford who with frank sinatra sang 
with the pied pipers in the tommy dorsey band 
he rich and sinatra were the darlings of the band they sort 
of locked heads fighting for the attention of the public tommy 
stood back and laughed in a weird way he encouraged this said 
torme who visited rich at home the afternoon before he died april 
2 1987 
he said he asked the drummer that day if he wanted the book to 
be a puff piece or warts and all he said warts and all just 
be accurate 
buddy had a mouth on him ive liberally quoted him torme 
said 
his dad had been a blackface comedian with minstrel shows at 
the turn of the century he was a hard taskmaster life was made 
very tough for buddy i feel his occasional abrasiveness came out 
of that he was extremely tough on his bands thats why they were 
superb he used to say i give 110 percent every night i expect 
nothing less from you when they did play well he was ecstatic 
when they dogged it he went bananas 
we occasionally had our outs one time i didnt talk to him 
for 2 years i allude to the argument without the hurtful 
quotes torme said 
i made the book as objective as i could make it im not 
settling old scores for him or with him he was wildly witty and 
if you believe the phrase his talent was godgiven 
torme said that rich as an infant was keeping time with a 
vaudeville band during a rehearsal the manager of the theater 
comes over why dont you put the kid in your act tonight 
buddys father carried him out by his belt put him in front of 
drums and they played stars and stripes forever they had to play 
it three times that night 
his vaudeville name until he was 12 was traps the drum 
wonder then he became buddy traps his real name was bernard 
rich the book will be published by oxford university press next 
fall torme intends to give richs grandson 30 percent of the 
profits 
tormes debut came with the band led by carleton coon and joe 
sanders at the blackhawk hotel in chicago my parents took me in 
to hear them one night joe sanders said to them why does this 
kid know all the tunes i can see he knows them tormes father 
explained hed heard them on the radio so on invitation the tiny 
torme sang youre driving me crazy 
i became a monday night feature made 15 every monday night 
and dinner for me and mom and dad my family was musical but not 
professional my mother whos 89 played piano and my dad 92 
danced 
rich and torme met in 1944 when rich sat in on hawaiian war 
chant with charlie spivaks band he played it as if hed 
played it all his life he had played a different arrangement with 
tommy dorsey he could sense everything 
the last time he played professionally was in january 1987 at 
the paladium in a show i hosted a salute to tommy dorsey the last 
thing he played was the dorsey arrangement of hawaiian war chant 
 
torme turned 65 in september the november issue of life 
magazine lists him among the nations six most enduring singers 
torme lives in beverly hills calif with his fourth wife ali 
he has five children ages ranging from 17 to 37 
while here for a months performances at michaels pub a table 
in his hotel room holds a small blender and packets of slim fast 
i started on it in may 1988 he said i just got to the point 
i wasnt comfortable in my clothes singing i was having trouble 
with breath control because i was too heavy 
he lost 35 pounds in eight months last year executives of slim 
fast whose offices are in the same building as michaels pub saw 
his show and invited him to make a tv commercial for them he did 
it after writing his own jingle 
tormes been busy this year he and george shearing performed at 
a new zealand jazz festival and he and cleo laine toured together 
during the summer torme also recorded the stephen sondheim song 
live alone and like it for warren beattys movie dick 
tracy 
torme the buddy rich band and the mcguire sisters will start an 
extensive us tour next february 
