albert einsteins letters and the example 
of couples like the curies contributed to the belief that his 
theory of relativity was a collaboration between einstein and his 
first wife 
evan harris walker a research physicist at the armys aberdeen 
proving grounds said there are a dozen instances in which einstein 
referred to our work in letters to his first wife mileva 
einsteinmaric 
it becomes clear from what he has to say himself that mileva 
played a significant role in the early work walker said 
recently 
several einstein historians disagree 
but louis pyenson a science historian at the university of 
montreal said such a collaboration would not be unusual 
considering the number of other wellknown husband and wife 
scientific teams at the turn of the century including marie and 
pierre curie known for their work in radioactivity 
walker said his theory also would help solve a puzzle over the 
development of his landmark theory einstein denied later in life 
that previous work on the speed of light by the american physicist 
albert michelson influenced his work 
walker said the influence likely came from einsteinmaric 
in one letter walker noted einstein wrote how happy and 
proud i will be when the two of us together will have brought our 
work on the relative motion to a victorious conclusion 
the letters were part of the einstein papers published in 1986 
by princeton university where he worked for several years 
the theory of relativity was the foundation for much of physics 
since einstein published three groundbreaking papers in 1905 that 
eventually led to his winning the nobel prize in 1921 the theory 
deals with the relationship between time and space and proposes 
that time moves slower for objects traveling at greater speeds 
i dont see that theres any evidence she contributed in the 
way they claim said clifford will a physics professor at the 
mcdonnell center for space science at washington university in st 
louis i guess they looked at some of the letters and tried to 
infer she was involved 
part of this is the myth that einstein needed help with 
mathematics and there is simply no evidence in his career that 
this is true will said the mathematics in relativity is 
simple all that was needed to develop the theory was physical 
insight the brilliant physical insight that einstein had 
einsteinmaric a mathematician and physicist was several years 
older than einstein who was in his early 20s when he began work on 
relativity and may have been the leader early on walker said 
the two met as students at the swiss federal institute of 
technology in zurich and were married in 1904 a year before 
einstein published the three papers strengthening walkers case is 
their 1919 divorce agreement in which einstein agreed his former 
wife would receive any nobel prize proceeds einstein might win 
