michelson had visited several years earlier 
without michelson the problem the theory of relativity would 
have answered wasnt there thats why physicists said the theory 
was puzzling walker said mileva was on the scene and had 
access to information of that sort and she probably played the role 
of inseminating those ideas 
light like other waves had been thought to require a medium 
dubbed the ether to travel through some physicists theorized that 
because earth was moving through this substance it would slow down 
or speed up light depending on the direction the light was 
traveling in relation to the ether 
michelsons experiments in the late 19th century compared the 
amount of time it took two beams of light pointed in different 
directions to travel from their source bounce off a mirror and 
return despite repeated attempts at increasing distances the 
times were always the same confusing scientists 
einsteins 1905 paper on the photoelectric effect of light 
disproved the ether theory 
on one paper she helped with the mathematics and on the 
papers on relativity and light she did something very 
fundamental walker said that she helped is beyond question 
its the degree of help 
einsteinmaric studied under phillip lenard a german physicist 
and most likely brought to einsteins attention lenards work on 
light walker said 
it is true we dont have any direct evidence for precisely 
which equation einsteins first wife told albert about that kind 
of information is seldom available pyenson said 
what does seem clear and there is no question is the pattern 
of young physicist couples in the 1900s is a clear trend in 
europe he said all you have to do is look at the curies 
