<TEXT>
the wife of genentech incs president has 
settled insider trading allegations that she tipped her brother 
about confidential merger talks the company was holding with roche 
holding ltd 
according to the securities and exchange commission mollie e 
raab did not trade for herself but her brother told a friend who 
allegedly made some 127400 in illegal profits 
genetech completed a merger with roche in september 
without admitting or denying wrongdoing mrs raab of 
hillsborough calif agreed to pay 162400 in penalties and 
interest to settle a civil action filed by the securities and 
exchange commission at federal court in san francisco on tuesday 
neither genentech nor mrs raabs husband g kirk raab chief 
executive officer of the san franciscobased pharmaceutical and 
biotechnology company were accused of any wrongdoing 
mrs raab did not profit on the stock trades raab said in a 
statement issued by genentech she knows it was wrong to have 
told her brother who was having prolonged financial difficulty 
and she accepts her penalty we are both sorry for any 
embarrassment this incident has caused to genentech and its 
employees the statement concluded 
also settling with the sec were mrs raabs brother michael 
gaylord painter and one of his friends joseph jeffries both of 
san antonio texas 
some of the circumstances in the case resemble the controversial 
insider trading case against broker robert chestman in new york 
a federal appeals court overturned chestmans conviction earlier 
this year on the grounds there was insufficent evidence chestman 
knew information he got from a family member of the waldbaum 
supermarket chain owners about a pending merger with aampp was 
confidential 
the government is appealing that court decision 
though the issues framed for litigation would have been 
interesting mr painter was not required to disgorge any money or 
to pay any penalty and under the circumstances he decided to 
dispose of the matter rather than engage in costly litigation 
said his lawyer washington attorney richard morvillo 
but harry weiss an associate director of the secs enforcement 
division said the misappropriation theory used in the raab case 
is not an issue in the chestman appeal 
in the chestman case said weiss the issue is the proof the 
government must offer to establish whether a person getting a 
confidential stock tip knows the tipster is illegally violating a 
trust or duty 
in the raab case were alleging sufficient evidence to 
establish the exisitence of a relationship and a breach of that 
relationship said weiss 
mrs raab is not an officer of the company but she has a 
relationship of trust and confidence with her husband the breach 
of that duty is the misappropriation with which she was 
charged 
weiss noted that in any event the defendants settled without 
going to trial 
the sec alleged that jeffries made about 127400 in illegal 
trading profits using the information painter got from his sister 
with the understanding that the two men would split it although 
lawyers declined to say whether painter actually ever took 
possession of any of the profits 
the sec also alleged that jeffries also told other people who 
made an additional 70000 in trading profits 
they were not accused of insider trading because there wasnt 
enough evidence to conclude they knew the information had been 
stolen said weiss 
as part of the settlement however jeffries will pay 133700 
in illegal profits plus interest the government waived additional 
penalties for him and painter after they gave sworn statements that 
they were unable to pay 
although there was no allegation mrs raab traded illegally for 
herself under the insider trading sanctions act however she 
could have been ordered to pay penalties equal to the profits made 
by those she tipped 
the 162400 she will pay was part of the negotiated settlement 
said weiss 
according to the sec complaint mrs raab learned about the 
merger negotiations from her husband and sometime between jan 22 
and feb 2 she told her brother to buy a few thousand dollars worth 
of genentech stock saying buy now even if he had to borrow 
money 
she told her brother good things were about to happen to 
genentech and that he should keep his purchase and her comments 
confidential according to the sec 
at the time genentech stock was trading at about 21 a share 
painter in turn told jeffries who bought option contracts to buy 
genentech securities which he agreed to split with painter an 
option contract is an agreement to buy stock at a later date for a 
fixed price if the price of the stock goes up before the contract 
date the buyer makes the difference in profit 
