chairman charles a corry said the move gives usx the flexibility 
for any steel restructuring 
palm said the unions request to match offers for the steel 
division must be dealt with before there can be agreement on a 
contract to replace the one that expires feb 1 no date is set for 
resuming the talks which broke off after the two sides failed to 
meet a selfimposed deadline on nov 10 
the union said it would swing the deal through an employee stock 
ownership plan a buyout technique that gained favor in the 1980s 
particularly in the steel industry 
weirton steel corp was created in 1984 when the west virginia 
steel makers 7700 employees bought the company from national 
steel for 386 million other employeeled buyouts in the industry 
include northwestern steel and wire of sterling ill republic 
engineered steels of massillon ohio and pittsburgh forgings 
usx spokesman thomas ferrall declined to comment on the unions 
request to match any offer for the steel unit but many analysts 
believe usx would balk at such a deal however several said the 
success of other steel employee stock ownership plans pressure 
from icahn the softening steel market and other factors might 
force usx to accede to an employee buyout 
