michael milken climbed quietly to the 
mountaintop of american finance his descent was much louder 
born and raised in california milken was a math whiz helping 
his fathers accounting business by age 10 he studied arcane 
business tracts while others marched for civil rights and peace 
during the 1960s in his early years on wall street milken 
digested financial documents during a twohour commute 
with the same passion milken avoided the limelight after 
gaining market prowess shunning interviews and refusing to pose 
alone for drexel burnham lambert incs annual report 
milken became a familiar figure only after named by speculator 
ivan boesky in the governments fraud investigation in late 1986 
the most prominent financier in the securities industry in the 
booming 1980s milken became prosecutors main target 
his quirky personality and stupefying wealth have contributed to 
widely divergent public views of the 44yearold financier 
