terms of the agreement were not disclosed closing is expected 
by the end of the year 
connecticutbased micrognosis supplies trading room systems for 
the financial services industry worldwide serving 250 banks 
insurance companies securities firms and major corporations from 
25 offices in 15 countries it had revenue of about 100 million in 
1989 
the companys approximately 430 employees most of whom work in 
danbury conn new york and london will be retained control data 
said 
micrognosis is a market leader in europe asia and the united 
states said lawrence perlman president and chief executive 
officer of control data with csks commitment to the market and 
to investing in micrognosis customers can be confident that 
micrognosis will continue to provide advanced trading systems and 
features as well as excellent service 
globalization is essential if csk is to achieve its goal of 
generating 10 billion in revenues by the year 2001 said isao 
okawa president and chairman of csk by acquiring micrognosis 
we are establishing an excellent foundation to do business beyond 
japan 
