per share for its most recent quarter ceased development of the 
very highspeed highdensity srams as part of a restructuring the 
losses included a restructuring charge of 143 million 
the hightech company announced in august that it would stop 
making computer chips at the washington plant and was laying off 
300 people leaving about 550 workers at the facility 
