<DOCNO> AP901121-0275 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
nutrasweet co officials were singing the blues 
wednesday about a federal appeals court decision that the pastel 
blue color of the companys equal brand sweetener packets is not a 
trademark 
nutrasweet based in north suburban deerfield went to court in 
february 1989 seeking to halt stadt corp and cumberland packing 
corps use of blue packets for their lowcalorie sweet one brand 
sweetener 
the us district court for the northern district of illinois 
denied nutrasweets motion for an injunction in the fall of 1989 
nutrasweet a division of monsanto co of st louis appealed the 
case to the seventh us circuit court of appeals which upheld the 
lower court ruling in a decision issued earlier this month 
nutrasweet spokesman rich nelson said the company is considering 
appealing the decision to the us supreme court 
we believe the use of color alone can be used as a tredemark 
just as other courts have found nelson said wednesday 
nutrasweets lawsuit contended that the blue packets in which it 
has packaged equal since 1982 distinguish the aspartame sweetener 
from other sugar substitutes such as sweet n low which comes in 
pink packets and sugar twin which is packaged in yellow 
nutrasweet conceded the sweet ones packets are not the same 
shade of blue as equals but said the color is confusingly 
similar to equals 
nutrasweet based its argument mainly on a 1985 federal appeals 
court ruling from another circuit in a case involving owenscorning 
fiberglas corp maker of pink fiberglass insulation in that case 
the court established a limited rule that in certain situations a 
particular color could be registered as a trademark 
in the nutrasweet decision senior district judge john w 
reynolds wrote that the general rule prohibiting registration of 
color as a trademark should continue to be the law in this 
circuit partly because changing the law would result in 
infringement actions that could soon degenerate into questions of 
shade confusion similar to the nutrasweet case 
how different do the colors have to be reynolds wrote 
under nutrasweets proposed test the only way to answer that 
question is through litigation 
officials of stadt and cumberland could not be reached wednesday 
for comment 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

